Phase 3 — BTC 15m Trading Engine

Phases 1 and 2 are complete. Platform foundation and plugin data/strategy layer all exist and import cleanly. Now build the actual trading engine — the bot.py that makes the 15-minute plugin trade.

Notes from Phase 1-2 review:
- plugin_state uses state_json TEXT blob (not individual columns). All state reads/writes must serialize/deserialize JSON. Use get_plugin_state("btc_15m") and update_plugin_state("btc_15m", {...}) from platform db.py. The update function should merge into the existing state_json, not replace it entirely.
- plugin_id is "btc_15m" everywhere. Config keys are namespaced: btc_15m.trading_mode, btc_15m.bet_size, etc.
- sys.path.insert(0, ...) is used in plugin files to fix imports. Keep this pattern consistent in bot.py.
- plugin.py has an asset_source property ("binance") — can use this if needed.
- The old codebase at /opt/15-min-btc-bot/bot.py is ~4,870 lines. Read it thoroughly for implementation details. Every nuance matters — skip paths, orphan recovery, shadow trades, Observatory feeding, FV model integration.

What to build:

1. plugins/btc_15m/bot.py — the full trading engine. This is the biggest file in this phase.

