Critical rules:
- Read old /opt/15-min-btc-bot/bot.py THOROUGHLY — it's ~4,870 lines and every nuance matters
- Observatory discard on shutdown — incomplete data MUST be discarded
- All 7 skip paths must use resolve_inline=True
- Regime snapshots >10 min old -> force regime to "unknown"
- Shadow trades: 60-second fill timeout, 1 contract only
- Skip-first-market after restart — always skip the current market on startup
- Orphan trade recovery on restart
- Consecutive error circuit breaker (5 errors -> stop auto-trading) — this one stays, it's a safety mechanism not a trading feature
- Fair value model: track BTC open price per market, refresh BTC price throttled, compute edge for idle display
- Observatory fed during BOTH idle polling AND active price polling
- Adaptive entry: starts below ask when spread >= 4c, walks up on retries
- Trailing stop: locks in gains once price reaches configurable % of target progress
- Early exit EV: exits losing trades when holding is negative EV with <2 min left
- Dynamic sell: FV model adjusts sell target mid-trade when FV shifts significantly
- python3 -m py_compile every modified file

Ask if anything is unclear before starting. At the end, summarize what was built, flag any judgment calls, and check in before Phase 4.
